With school back in session, Team 2539, the Krypton Cougars, will be having our programming workshop starting this 2024-09-09T04:00:00Z . Anyone is welcome to participate by joining our GoogleMeet, but it is targeted at beginners.

We will start with the basics of programming a robot in Java and move on to more advanced topics such as vision, autos, and how we implement swerve. The workshop will be in 6 sessions Monday and Wednesday each week for three weeks. Each day starts at 6:15 PM EST with about a 1 hour explainer for teaching, with about 2 hours afterwards for the lab, where you can put the knowledge to use and also ask questions, ending at 9:00 PM EST.

If you are interested, here is the signup:

This year we will be hosting our programming workshop in person and virtually online.  Starting September 9th on Mondays and Wednesdays at 6pm.

Some more information will be sent out in an email Saturday to anyone who signs up. If you have any questions just leave a response.

Thanks, Matthew Milunic 2539 Programming Lead
